# Marketing content — use project skills

When the task involves **marketing content, campaigns, brand voice, SEO, email sequences, competitive messaging, or performance reporting**, you MUST load and follow the matching skill from this repo before drafting or changing copy/strategy.

## Skills (official Anthropic `knowledge-work-plugins` / marketing)

| Task | Skill folder |
|------|----------------|
| Write/adapt channel copy | `content-creation` and/or `draft-content` |
| Campaign brief / calendar | `campaign-plan` |
| Brand / voice / style check | `brand-review` |
| Competitor positioning | `competitive-brief` |
| SEO audit / keywords / gaps | `seo-audit` |
| Nurture / drip emails | `email-sequence` |
| Channel performance report | `performance-report` |

Locations (same content): `.agents/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` and `.cursor/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`.

## How to apply

1. Read the relevant `SKILL.md` (and any linked files in that skill folder).
2. Follow its inputs, structure, and quality bar.
3. Prefer `/draft-content`, `/campaign-plan`, `/brand-review`, `/seo-audit`, etc. when the user invokes them.

## Content Stack product constraints (do not override)

- AI drafts → user reviews → admin approves → export. Nothing unapproved is published.
- Do not flip `*_LIVE` / live provider flags or touch production without explicit user yes.
- CC data access stays through `@/lib/db` (async); material actions `await logAction(...)`.
